I love Five Guy's burgers.  They're one of the reasons why I cannot give up meat. I like that the burgers are made to order when you place the order. The meat is not a hard formed frozen party full of chemicals. The difference is definitely obvious in the taste.  You can customize your sandwich from a large selection of fresh toppings: green peppers, jalepenos, lettuce, mushrooms,  onions grilled, or raw, or both, pickles, tomatoes, and  the usual condiment selection: hot sauce, ketchup, mayo, mustard,  relish,and steak sauce. The staff are polite and friendly.  I am not a big fan of dining in due to the small dining room that is slightly reminiscent of a 50's dinner with black & white tiles and bright red walls. They serve milkshakes and even BLT's, Grilled Cheese, Veggie  Sandwiches & hotdogs but I cannot imagine they sell nearly as many hot dogs as burgers.  Maybe here in Chicago just because they're one of the basic food groups in this city. There is always a crowd and limited seating.  Now, if you really love the food and can't wait to eat when you go home or back to the office I suggest securing a table while your food is prepared.  If you like fresh fries save your fat grams and or weekly  carbs for the week.  The small order of fries called a  little order is anything but.  I  feel like it's enough for two people unless its a teen with a bottomless pit for a stomach.  I  could quite possibly eat just fries if I've had a recent fix of the burger. The price of a burger and fries are about 3-4 more than McDonald's if you go with the little burger and little fries. Again,  don't let the name fool you! The price difference is truly worth it when compaing the quality of the food! I definitely recomend giving them a try if you haven't.
